   "body" : "When QT launches, move the following QSettings to `bitcoin.conf`:\r\n\r\n-`lang` (language)\r\n-`dbcache` (nDatabaseCache)\r\n-`par` (nThreadsScriptVerif)\r\n-`spendzeroconfchange` (bSpendZeroConfChange)\r\n-`upnp` (fUseUPnP)\r\n-`listen` (fListen)\r\n-`proxy` (fUseProxy)\r\n-`onion` (fUseSeparateProxyTor)\r\n\r\nBased on @luke-jr's #11082 and #7510\r\n\r\nThis is a step towards being able to configure `prune` from the GUI (#6461). Being able to write `bitcoin.conf` adds some complexity, but at the same time reducing reliance on QSettings removes some complexity.\r\n\r\nThere's potentially a safety benefit in storing  `listen`, `proxy` and `onion` in `bitcoin.conf` in case the user ever decides to run `bitcoind`.\r\n\r\nTODO:\r\n- [ ] `upnp`, `listen`, `proxy`, `onion`\r\n- [ ] handle malformed bitcoin.conf error\r\n- [ ] add release note\r\n- [ ] reset GUI options behavior",
